SUMMARY:Two Strangers (Carry a Cake Across New York)
LOCATION:Longacre Theatre, 220 West 48th Street, New York NY 10036
DESCRIPTION:<p>A <em>New York Times</em> Critics&rsquo; Pick, <em>Two
  Strangers (Carry a Cake Across New York)</em> &ldquo;delivers lavishly on
  laughter, escape, and fantasy.&rdquo;<br /><br />Meet Dougal, an
  impossibly upbeat Brit who has just landed in New York City for the first
  time to attend the wedding of the father he&rsquo;s never met. Meet Robin,
  the sister of the bride and a no-nonsense New Yorker with a lot of errands
  to do for the bride&mdash;including picking up the groom&rsquo;s estranged
  son from the airport.<br /><br />These two strangers begin their journey
  together navigating New York City, secrets, and second chances. <em>The
  Boston Globe</em> proclaims, it&rsquo;s &ldquo;Irresistible! Clever,
  funny, and delightfully surprising!&rdquo;<br /><br />&ldquo;An
  effervescent new musical comedy! Delivers lavishly on laughter, escape,
  and fantasy.&rdquo; &mdash; <em>The New York Times</em><br /><br
  />&ldquo;It&rsquo;s going to be stuck in your head for days. Absolutely
  charming.&rdquo; &mdash; Entertainment Weekly<br /><br />&ldquo; Achieves
  something magical.&rdquo; &mdash; <em>Vulture</em></p>
END:VEVENT
